headline: Jones Soda, Bethesda Softworks' highly sought after Vault-Tec Supply Packs are dropping at Costco Clubs across the United States just in time to make gamers' holidays
summary: Jones Soda Co. (CSE: JSDA) (OTCQB: JSDA) ("Jones Soda" or the "Company"), - The Fallout™-themed Vault-Tec Supply Pack's first run sold out just days after pallets first hit the floor at select Costco Warehouse Clubs in the United States' Northeast in October. The multi-flavored 12-packs include three game-inspired soda flavors and are bundled with the kind of Fallout collectibles that the franchise's fans love.

headline: Has Costco’s Premium Price Still Got Room To Run After Recent Share Pullback?
summary: If you are wondering whether Costco Wholesale at around $922 a share is still a smart buy or if the value story has already played out, you are not alone. headline: Clients Want the Everything-Store Experience
summary: The financial industry and clients have been trying to replicate that one-stop shopping experience for portfolios.  Advised households tend to use multiple shops, having a full service account with their wealth manager, as well as a self-directed brokerage account at another firm.  More and more, clients are looking to consolidate their assets and services under one roof, which can be quite a tall task for firms.
